 should inspect the BadRequest builder to see how it initializes the FieldAccessorTable inside newBuilder. There’s a lot happening here, and I want to make sure I’m following the logic correctly. Let’s take a closer look!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DVI9Ccdoh6IULXAFH0pgJHT4|fc_0cd0d6549e255c84016a23d2441b188190abc518532830541a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"internalGetFieldAccessorTable|newBuilderForType|FieldAccessorTable\" ../../source_context/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-common-protos/2.59.0/main/extracted/com/google/rpc/BadRequest.java | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 793, "output": 643, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35228, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780732464930, "responseId": "resp_0cd0d6549e255c84016a23d2319bc88190aa9ad25e65c79da6"}}
